\pard \plain \pard \keepn \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf2\b Installing Help Files Using GUI Application\plain\f0\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 To install a help file into the Delphi IDE do the following:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 1)\tab Select the Install tab. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 2)\tab Enter the name of the Help file to be installed in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Help file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  edit box. (You can include a {\strike file path macro}{\v FILEPATHMACROS} in the file path). Alternatively click the adjacent browse button to choose the file from a dialog box). 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 3)\tab If you wish to copy the help file to a different location before installing then enter the path the file is to be copied to in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Copy to\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  edit box. (You can include a {\strike file path macro}{\v FILEPATHMACROS} in the file path). Alternatively click the adjacent \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Browse\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  button and choose the folder from a dialog box).
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 4)\tab Enter a description of the help file in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  edit box - this is displayed when Delphi offers a choice of topics.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 5)\tab Choose the version you are installing into from the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  combo box.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 6)\tab Click the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Install\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  button.
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
