\pard \plain \pard \keepn \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf2\b Uninstalling Help Files Using GUI Application\plain\f0\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 To uninstall a help file from the Delphi IDE do the following:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 1)\tab Select the Remove tab.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 2)\tab Choose the help file from the drop-down list (CHI can only remove help files installed using the program and they are all listed here).
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 3)\tab If you wish Windows to forget about the help file's location check the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Remove file reference from registry\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  check box. You may not wish to do this if the help file is used by some other application.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 4)\tab If you want CHI to delete the help file check the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delete the help file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  check box. You can only do this if the file reference is also to be removed from the registry.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 5)\tab Choose the version you are uninstalling from using the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  combo box.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 6)\tab Click the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Remove\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  button.
