\pard \plain \pard \keepn \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf2\b Using the Command Line Application\plain\f0\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 A command line tool, \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 , comes bundled with \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Component Help Installer\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 . It integrates or de-integrate\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 s\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i OpenHelp\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  compatible help files with \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  v3\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  to v7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 . The purpose of this tool is to enable component help files to be installed in \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  from batch files, installers etc.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b Modes of operation\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  has three modes of operation:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 1)\tab {\strike installing help files}{\v CMDLINEINSTALL} into the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  IDE.
\par 2)\tab {\strike uninstalling help files}{\v CMDLINEUNINSTALL} registered by the GUI application\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 or \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 .
\par 3)\tab {\strike displaying help information}{\v CMDLINEHELP} on the console.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 To simplify installation and uninstallation on different versions of \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 , \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  supports the use of {\strike file path macros}{\v FILEPATHMACROS}.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b Return codes\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 If \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  successfully completes an installation / uninstallation then the program returns 0 to the operating system or calling program. If an error is encountered a positive number is returned.
