\pard \plain \pard \keepn \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf2\b Installing Help Files Using The Command Line\plain\f0\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This topic describes how to install help files using the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 command line tool.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  can:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 a)\tab copy help files to the required installation folder
\par b)\tab register the help file with Windows
\par c)\tab record a description of the file that appears in help find dialogs
\par d)\tab work with any version of Delphi from v3 onwards
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 The command to issue to install a help file \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 (all on one line) \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 is:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \li400 \keep \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 CHInst [-i] \plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i source_help_file\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \li800 \keep [-c \plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i dest_help_file\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 ]\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 [-d \plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i description\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 ] [-v\plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i X\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 ] [-q]\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 The switches and parameters are described below.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -i switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This switch is optional. It tells \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  to perform an installation rather than an uninstallation. Leaving the switch out has the same effect as including it. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 If provided the -i switch must be the first item on the command line. \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i source_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  specifies the name of the help file to be installed. This parameter is compulsory and must follow the -i switch where provided, or be the first parameter if the -i switch is omitted.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i source_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  path can include a {\strike file path macro}{\v FILEPATHMACROS}.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -c switch
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 If the -c switch is used then \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i source_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  is copied to \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i dest_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  and \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i dest_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  is registered with the Delphi IDE. If the -c switch is not used then the help file given by \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i source_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  is registered with Delphi and integrated into the IDE.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i dest_help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  path can include a file path macro.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -d switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This switch registers the following parameter as a \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i description\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  of the help file with the Delphi IDE. The \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i description\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  appears in topic list dialogs. (The \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i description\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  parameter must be enclosed in "" quotes if it contains spaces).
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -v switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This switch tells \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  which version of Delphi the help file is to be registered with. Replace \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i X\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  with the version of Delphi required - from 2 to \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 , e.g. -v5 for Delphi 5. If this switch is not provided then Delphi 4 is assumed.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -q switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This switch makes the program operate without generating any screen output. This is useful when calling \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  from batch files or installers where no screen output is required.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
