\pard \plain \pard \keepn \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf2\b Uninstall Help Files Using The Command Line\plain\f0\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This topic describes how to uninstall help files using the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  command line tool.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  can uninstall (de-integrate) help files from \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 . It can optionally delete the help file and / or unregister it with Windows. The program can only be used to uninstall help files that were installed using version 2 or later of the GUI application or command line tool.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 The command to issue unistall a previusly installed help file is:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \li400 \keep \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 CHInst -u \plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i help_file\plain\f3\fs18\cf0  [-r] [-x] [-v\plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i X\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 ]\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 The switches and parameters are described below.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -u switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This switch is required for uninstallation. The following \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  name specifies the path and file name of the file being uninstalled. The -u switch must be the first item on the command line.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i help_file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  name can include a {\strike file path macro}{\v FILEPATHMACROS}.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -r switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 Use this switch if the help file is to be unregistered with Windows (i.e. its entry is deleted from the registry).
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -x switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This switch causes the help file to be physically deleted. Use with care.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -v switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This switch tells \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  which version of \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  the help file is to be uninstalled from. Replace \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i X\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  with the version of \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  required - from 2 to \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 , e.g. -v5 for \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi 5\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 . If this switch is not provided then \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi 4\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  is assumed.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b the -q switch\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 This switch makes the program operate without generating any screen output. This is useful when calling \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  from batch files or (un)installers where no screen output is required.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
