\pard \plain \pard \keepn \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf2\b Getting Help For The Command Line Tool\plain\f0\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  can be requested to display help about using the program\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 . There are two types of help available by issuing the following commands.\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-1400 \li1800 \tx1800 \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 CHInst -h\plain\f4\fs18\cf0 \tab displays the CHI Windows help file at the "{\strike Using the Command Line Application}{\v USINGCMDLINE}" topic.
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i or\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  
\par \pard \fi-1400 \li1800 \tx1800 \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 CHInst -?\plain\f4\fs18\cf0 \tab displays a brief description of the command line parameters on the console.
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 No other parameters should be provided.
