${\footnote {$}Command Line Application Example}
#{\footnote {#}EXAMPLECMDLINE}
K{\footnote {K}Command line application;Command line application,example}
@{\footnote {@}Using CHI CNT topic: Example of using the command line application.}

\pard \plain \pard \keepn \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf2\b Command Line Application\plain\f1\fs24\cf2\b  Example\plain\f0\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 In this example we'll create a batch file to install the DelphiDabbler Version Information component's help file into a selected version of Delphi. (A copy of the component is available from the \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 DelphiDabbler website\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 ).
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 We will pass the required version as a parameter to the batch file, along with a switch indicating whether to install or uninstall. We will also flag up any errors. The batch file assumes that the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i TPJVersionInfo\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  help file - \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 PJVersionInfo.hlp\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  has been copied to the system's TEMP folder which we find by accessing the %TEMP% environment variable from the batch file.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 Here's the batch file (the line numbers are for reference only and are not part of the file. Note that some lines below have had to be folded over to display all the required information - they should be entered all on one line. The batch file needs to be executed from the same folder as the CHInst program.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \keep \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 01  @echo off
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 02  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 if "%1" == "" goto err1
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 03  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 if "%2" == "" goto err2
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 04  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 if "%1" == "install" goto install
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 05  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 if "%1" == "uninstall" goto uninstall
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 06  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 goto err1
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 07  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 :install
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 08  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 chinst -i "%TEMP%\\PJVersionInfo.hlp" -q -c 
\par     $(HELP)\\PJVI.hlp 
\par     -d "Delphi Dabbler Version Info Component" -v%2 
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 09  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 if ERRORLEVEL 1 goto errinst
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 10  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 echo File installed to Delphi %2
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 11  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 goto end
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 12  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 :uninstall
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 13  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 chinst -u $(HELP)\\PJVI.hlp -q -r -x -v%2
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 14  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 if ERRORLEVEL 1 goto errinst
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 15  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 echo File uninstalled from Delphi %2
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 16  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 goto end
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 17  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 :errinst
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 18  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 echo CHINST return error %ERRORLEVEL%
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 19  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 goto end
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 20  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 :err1
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 21  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 echo First parameter must be "install" or "uninstall"
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 22  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 goto end
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 23  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 :err2
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 24  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 echo 2nd parameter (Delphi version) required
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 25  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 :end
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 The batch file works as follows:
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 \tab Lines 01 to 07 simply check the parameters are OK. 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 \tab In lines 08 to 11 we attempt to install the help file and trap any error results (CHI returns > 0 on error) or report OK and end. Note we use a {\strike path macro}{\v FILEPATHMACROS} to install into the required \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 Help\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  folder. We also use the %TEMP% environment variable to find the location of the temporary folder that contains the help file.
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 \tab Lines 12 to 16 are where the uninstallation is performed and either success or error are reported. Note that we are both removing the help file's registry entry (-r) and deleting the file copy (-x) - so be careful not to use this script where a help file is installed in >1 version of Delphi. 
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 \tab Lines 17 to 19 are used to report any error codes returned from the program, while lines 20 to 24 report any problems with parameters.
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 .\plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \brdrt \brdrs  
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i See also:\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
