\pard \plain \pard \keepn \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf2\b How CHI Works\plain\f0\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b Overview\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHI\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  works quite simply by \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 updating \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  help \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 configuration file\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 s\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 with \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 statements required to integrate the help file with the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi OpenHelp\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  system. \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi's\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  help contents file is then modified \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 as necessary \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 to refer to the configuration file\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 s\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 . \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  also maintains a small configuration file to record which help files it has installed. \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 The  registry is also updated to register the help file and its path with Windows.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\b Please note\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  that, in order to ensure that \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  takes note of the changes made when installing and uninstalling, \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  deletes any existing \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .gid\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  and \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .ftg\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  files in the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 Help\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  folder. Since \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .ftg\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  files store any word indexes used by the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i Find\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  tab in \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i WinHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 , these indexes will need to be rebuilt after installing component help files.\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b Installation Details\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  updates the following \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  files, stored in the \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 Help\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  sub folder of the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  installation. (where \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i X\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  is the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  version number):
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \tx2000 \tx3600 \brdrb \brdrs \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i Delphi 3..6\tab Delphi 7\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \tx2000 \tx3600 \plain\f1\fs8\cf0  \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 Help contents file\tab \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 delphi\plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i X\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .cnt\tab d7.cnt
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 OpenHelp link file\tab \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 delphi\plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i X\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .ohi\tab d7.ohi
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 OpenHelp index file\tab \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 delphi\plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i X\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .ohl\tab d7.ohl
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 CHI Config file\tab \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 CHId\plain\f3\fs18\cf0\i X\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .cfg\tab CHId7.cfg
\par \pard \brdrt \brdrs \plain\f1\fs8\cf0  \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 For Delphi 6 and 7 \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  also updates the compiler's \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .als\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  file. In Delphi 6 this is \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 delphi6.als\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  and in Delphi 7 it is \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 d7.als\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 . This is only done if there an .als file in the same folder as the help file and it has the same name.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 The files are update as follows, asumming \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 we are installing a file named \plain\f5\fs18\cf0 MyHelpFile.hlp\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  into \plain\f5\fs18\cf0 C:\\MyHelpFolder\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  with a \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 description \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 of \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 "My Description"\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 :
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 If it doesn't already exist the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  config file is created. \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Users should never edit this file manually.\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab The following entr\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 y is\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  added to \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  config file:\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li1200 \tx400 \plain\f5\fs18\cf0 :\plain\f6\fs18\cf0 Installed\plain\f5\fs18\cf0  MyHelpFile.hlp
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 The Help contents file is updated to reference the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  link and index files by ensuring the file contains the following lines:\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li1200 \tx400 \plain\f7\fs18\cf0 :Include delphi4.ohi
\par :Include delphi4.ohl\plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 The following line is added to the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  link file:
\par \pard \fi-400 \li1200 \tx400 \plain\f7\fs18\cf0 :\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 Link\plain\f7\fs18\cf0  \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 MyHelpFile\plain\f7\fs18\cf0 .\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 hlp\plain\f7\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 The following line is added to the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  index file:
\par \pard \fi-400 \li1200 \tx400 \plain\f7\fs18\cf0 :\plain\f3\fs18\cf0 Index My Description=MyHelpFile.hlp\plain\f7\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab A string value named \plain\f5\fs18\cf0 MyHelpFile.hlp\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  with value \plain\f5\fs18\cf0 C:\\MyHelpFolder \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 is added to the \plain\f5\fs18\cf0 HK\plain\f6\fs18\cf0 LM\plain\f5\fs18\cf0 \\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Help\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  registry key:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f4\fs18\cf0 \tab In Delphi 6 and 7 \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .als\plain\f4\fs18\cf0  files are merged into to the main \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 .als\plain\f4\fs18\cf0  file.\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b Uninstallation Details\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHI\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  should only be used to uninstall files that is has installed\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  - i.e the files that are listed in the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i CHI\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  config file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 . The\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 se\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  files \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 are \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 displayed on the Remove page of the Windows application. When a help file is uninstalled \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 the following actions take place:
\par \plain\f1\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 \tab The relevant \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 :Index\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  entry is removed from the \plain\f1\fs18\cf0\i OpenHelp\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  index file
