${\footnote {$}File Path Macros}
#{\footnote {#}FILEPATHMACROS}
K{\footnote {K}File path macros}
@{\footnote {@}General sub-topic: explains use of file path macros in the GUI and command line versions of CHI.}

\pard \plain \pard \keepn \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs24\cf2\b File Path Macros\plain\f0\fs20\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0  
\par \pard 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 To assist in accessing files in Delphi's folders (the usual location for help files is in the Help subfolder of a Delphi installation), the following macros can be included at the start of file names  These macros work with the Windows application\plain\f1\fs18\cf0  and \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i CHInst\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  command line tool.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab \plain\f5\fs18\cf0 $(ROOT)\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  - this macro is replaced by the path to the root folder of the Delphi installation.
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab \plain\f5\fs18\cf0 $(HELP)\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  - this macro is replaced by the path to the help folder of the Delphi installation.
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 In both cases the installation accessed is the selected version of Delphi. How the version is determined depends on the tool being used:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Windows application:\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  the version of Delphi selected in the combo box.
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Command line tool:\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  the version of Delphi specified in the -v command line switch.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 To use file path macros in the GUI, simply enter them at the start of a path name in the relevant edit box. To use on the command line type the macro name at the start of  a file name.
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b Example using command line tool\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 To install a help file that has been unzipped into \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 C:\\Unzip\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  into Delphi \plain\f1\fs18\cf0 6\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 's help folder, using the command line tool use:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \li400 \keep \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 CHInst -i C:\\Unzip\\MyHelp.hlp -c\plain\f4\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \li800 \keep \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 $(HELP)\\MyHelp.hlp -v6\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 -d "My Help Description"\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 ensuring the command is all entered on one line.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 And, to uninstall the file use
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \li400 \keep \plain\f3\fs18\cf0 CHInst -u $(HELP)\\  MyHelp.hlp -r -x -v3\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs12\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\b Example using Windows application\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 To perform the same installation as above, select the install page and:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \fi-400 \li400 \tx400 \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab Enter \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i C:\\Unzip\\MyHelp.hlp\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Help file\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  edit box\plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i .\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab Enter \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i $(HELP)\\MyHelp.hlp\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Copy to\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  edit box.
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab Select \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i 3\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Delphi\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  combo box.
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf0 \'A7\plain\f0\fs18\cf0 \tab Click the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Install\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  button.
\par \pard \tx400 \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 Uninstallation is acheived by selecting the installed file from the combo box on the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Remove\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  page and clicking the \plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i Remove\plain\f0\fs18\cf0  button.\plain\f0\fs18\cf0\i 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf0 
\par \pard \brdrt \brdrs  \plain\f0\fs18\cf0 
